Cum iter ad mare cepísset, * pópulus voce magna clamábat: Dómine Jesu Christe, salva illum; et Clemens cum lácrimis dicébat: Súscipe, Pater, spíritum meum.
As he began to move towards the sea, * the people cried with a loud voice: Save him, O Lord Jesus Christ; and Clement weeping said: Father, receive my spirit.
